**
** CompDam parameters
**
** The next two cards define parameter tables for CompDam parameters
** These should not be modified.
*PARAMETER TABLE TYPE, NAME=KEY_FLOAT, parameters=2
STRING
FLOAT
*PARAMETER TABLE TYPE, NAME=KEY_INT, parameters=2
STRING
INTEGER
** Define the parameter "table collection" which can include two
** tables: one for float parameters and one for integer parameters
*TABLE COLLECTION, NAME=COMPDAM_PARAM
** CompDam parameters with float values
*PARAMETER TABLE, type=KEY_FLOAT, label=CDP_FLOAT
** tol_DGD_f, tol_DGD/YT
tol_DGD_f, 1.d-4
**
** minimum amount of damage dissipated per MD increment
dGdGc_min, 1.d-12
**
** minimum accepted det(F_bulk)
compLimit, 0.25d0
**
** penalty stiffness multiplier
penStiffMult, 1.d3
**
** artificially slow rate of change of F_bulk
cutback_amount, 0.5d0
**
** Tolerance for divergence of internal Newton Raphson loop
tol_divergence, 1.d-6
**
** Maximum shear strain; when this value is exceeded, the element is deleted
gamma_max, 4.d0
**
** Ratio of kink band size to element length at which to decompose the element
kb_decompose_thres, 0.99d0
**
** Angle at which fiber failure occurs; no further plastic shear deformation allowed
fkt_fiber_failure_angle, -1.d0
**
** Tolerance value used to determine if convergence has occurred in newton raphson loop
schaefer_nr_tolerance, 1.d-6
**
** Time at which to kill analysis (for debugging purposes)
debug_kill_at_total_time, -1.d0
**
** Initial fiber misalignment azimuthal average [degrees]
fkt_init_misalignment_azi_mu, 0.d0
**
** Initial fiber misalignment azimuthal variance [degrees]
fkt_init_misalignment_azi_sigma, 45.d0
**
** Initial fiber misalignment polar shape parameter [degrees]
fkt_init_misalignment_polar_shape, 0.676d0
**
** Initial fiber misalignment polar standard deviation [degrees]
fkt_init_misalignment_polar_scale, 2.25d0
**
** R ratio for cohesive fatigue model, sigma_min / sigma_max
fatigue_R_ratio, 0.1d0
**
** Fatigue cycles per solution increment
cycles_per_increment_init, 1.d-4
**
** Maximum fatigue cycles per solution increment
cycles_per_increment_max, 1.d5
**
** Minimum fatigue cycles per solution increment
cycles_per_increment_min, 1.d-5
**
** Percent change to fatigue cycles per solution increment when rate of energy dissipation is out-of-range
cycles_per_increment_mod, 0.1d0
**
** thresholds for fatigue damage progression per solution increment in terms of percent fracture toughness
fatigue_damage_min_threshold, 5.d-6
fatigue_damage_max_threshold, 1.d-4
**
**
** CompDam parameters with integer values
** 0=False, 1=True
*PARAMETER TABLE, type=KEY_INT, label=CDP_INT
** Logger level
** 1=errors only, 2=warnings, 3=info, 4=debug (very small models only)
logLevel, 2
**
** 1=default (to log file)
logFormat, 1
**
** DGD maximum number of cut-backs
cutbacks_max, 4
**
** DGD maximum number of damage increments per solution increment
MD_max, 1000
**
** DGD maximum number of equilibrium iterations
EQ_max, 1000
**
** Set to true (1) to search for the matrix crack angle with maximum failure index
alpha_search, 1
**
** increment, in degrees, for which the matrix failure criterion is evaluated
alpha_inc, 10
**
** maximum matrix crack angle alpha, in degrees
alpha_max, 60
**
** maximum number of Newton-Raphson loops before divergence is assumed
schaefer_nr_counter_limit, 10000000
**
** Set to false (0) to trigger a warning, delete the element, and allow the analysis to continue when no converged solution can be found
terminate_on_no_convergence, 1
**
** Set to true (1) to use the time as the seed for initial fiber misalignment to get different results for each realization
fkt_random_seed, 0
**
** Step number for fatigue analysis
fatigue_step, 100000
**
** Set to true (1) to check for constitutive snap-back
check_for_snap_back, 0
**